      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must be verified under an ISO 9001-compliant QMS with documented regression test suite covering all active turbulence closures.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R2) is developed under an ISO 9001 QMS. Regression tests cover the SST k-omega closure used in this model, but documentation of test coverage for the hemolysis scalar transport sub-model is incomplete. Achieved level 3; required level 4 for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy testing via manufactured solutions for all governing equations including the hemolysis power-law transport equation.",
      "rationale": "Order-of-accuracy tests confirm second-order spatial accuracy for momentum and continuity. The hemolysis power-law source term was not included in the manufactured-solution suite. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 2% for hemolysis index QoI on a minimum three-level refinement study.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed; GCI for NIH is 4.7%, exceeding the 2% threshold. Achieved level 3; gap persists at MRL 5 requirement of level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid temperature) must match COU operating envelope within ±5%.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro loop tests were conducted at 37 °C ± 1 °C and target flow rates ± 3.5%. Rotational speed was controlled within ± 20 RPM. Temperature and flow rate tolerances are within ±5%, but only 3 of 5 target operating points were physically achievable in the loop. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E_rel) documented for all QoIs with uncertainty bounds from both simulation and experiment.",
      "rationale": "Relative error and expanded uncertainty intervals are reported for NIH at all tested operating points. Simulation uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo (500 samples). Experimental uncertainty from repeat runs (n=5). Combined metric documented but interval overlap analysis not performed. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation QoIs must include the primary clinical endpoint (NIH) and at least one intermediate fluid-mechanical QoI (e.g., wall shear stress distribution).",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly compared. Velocity field (PIV) serves as an intermediate QoI. Wall shear stress distribution is reported from simulation but not compared to independent experimental data. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, fluid (bovine blood or equivalent), and operating envelope as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry and bovine blood at physiological hematocrit. Operating conditions span 4 of 5 COU flow-speed pairs. The fifth operating point (highest speed, lowest flow) was not experimentally validated due to loop pressure limitations. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual tolerance < 1e-6 for all equations; round-off error assessed for double-precision arithmetic.",
      "rationale": "Residuals for momentum and continuity reach 1e-5; hemolysis scalar residual stalls at 5e-5 for the highest-speed operating point. Double-precision confirmed. Achieved level 2; required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation protocol with independent peer review of setup parameters and boundary condition assignments.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup document exists and was reviewed internally. No independent external peer review of boundary condition assignments was performed. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification of turbulence closure and hemolysis damage model selection with sensitivity analysis across at least two alternative model forms.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega selected based on prior FDA pump benchmark literature. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law used without comparison to alternative damage models (e.g., Arora RBC model). No model-form sensitivity study performed. Achieved level 2; required level 4 represents a significant gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation performed; input sensitivity ranking documented.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed over 500 samples for blood viscosity, hemolysis model coefficients, and inlet flow rate. However, the rheological input data originate from the 2018 dataset (dataVintage 2018-03-15), which predates the current model revision (2026-01-10). No re-characterisation of blood rheology was performed after the model build was updated; the impact of any model-form changes on the validity of the 2018 rheological fit has not been assessed. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Biological variability in blood properties characterised across a minimum of three independent donor samples with documented hematocrit and plasma protein levels.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro tests used bovine blood from two independent draws. Hematocrit controlled to 33% ± 2%. Plasma protein characterisation not reported. Minimum three-sample requirement not met. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal equivalency mapping between experimental and simulation input parameters documented, including non-dimensionalisation and scaling arguments where applicable.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles and rotational speed are directly matched between experiment and simulation. Fluid viscosity is matched via Carreau-Yasuda fit to the 2018 rheology dataset. No formal equivalency document exists; scaling arguments for the hemolysis model coefficients between bovine and human blood are not provided. Achieved level 2."
    }
